STATE_WATERSHED_RULES: In April of 2010, a legislative bill (HF2459) outlining the process for establishing formal Watershed Management Authorities was signed into Iowa law. The bill calls on watershed stakeholders to sign 28E joint intergovernmental agreements to reduce flood risk and improve water quality, monitor federal flood risk planning and activities, and educate residents of the watershed regarding flood risks and water quality (Rebuild Iowa Office 2010).
